VETERAN COURT

Parties are prepared to enter into a Veteran's Treatment Court Deferred Prosecution Agreement.

Defendant was advised of constitution rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights and entered a plea of GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to the plea.  Stipulation by parties to complaint as a factual basis to sustain the guilty plea.  Defendant further advised that if he is not a US citizen deportation is possible.  Court found the defendant guilty as charged in the Complaint/Information.  Court WITHHELD entry of judgment of conviction.  Deferred Prosecution Agreement received, signed and filed.

No use or possession of any dangerous weapons or firearms
No application for CCW permit

Defendant Jordan D Roberts in court.  Attorney Christopher Lee Hartley in court for Jordan D Roberts.  Prosecuting attorney Brad Alan Vorpahl in court for the State of Wisconsin. Deputy court clerk cmt. 
Defendant Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defense waived reading and momentarily enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of client.
Review hearing scheduled for November 30, 2022 at 10:50 am.
